Bonjour,
*Merci de transmettre cette offre de stage à vos étudiants*

OVERVIEW

The objective of this internship is to modelise and develop a (small) ontology and associated information extraction tools for the intelligence domain in the case of assymetric warfare,
The internship will first consist in building and developing a ontology of events in this domain with the associated vocabulary in english and french.
Then to propose and develop linguistic pattern and rules (in english and french) to extract information regarding these events on a dedicated corpus
(kind of events based on the domain ontology, geolocalisation, datation and people linked to the event)

SKILLS :

Studies in Computer Science
Good Knowledge of Computationnal Linguistics (GATE and JAPE rules skills appreciated)
Good Knowledge of Semantic Web Technologies (RDF,OWL and Protege tool)
Knowledge of Web technologies, such as XML, Web Services, SOA appreciated

OTHER

6 months min. starting early 2010
Paid Intership located in Val de Reuil (Normandie France)


Khaled Khelif

